Comments.Message:
I too have this problem
My file is attached too: Is there a list of character profilers out there or is it just rpgo-character profiler:

Basically RAWR throws an exception when looking up a key in a dictionary - no call stack or anything to report, so just attached my lua as requested. 
An additional problem is once this happens you cant close the status dialog; you have to close the main form - annoying.

Details of add-on:

## Interface: 30100
## Title: rpgo-CharacterProfiler
## Notes: Export Character Profiles for use out-of-game
## Version: 3.1.0
## Author: calvin
## X-Date: May 20, 2009
## X-Email: calvin@rpgoutfitter.com
## X-Publisher: RPG Outfitter
## X-Website: http://www.rpgoutfitter.com/CharacterProfiler/
## SavedVariables: rpgoCPpref,myProfile
## License: http://rpgoutfitter.com/addons/license.cfm

Ok - I've debugged the code and found the exporter doesn't list the talents. 

SavedVariablesDictionary talent_tree = characterInfo["Talents"] as SavedVariablesDictionary;
323: Rawr.CharacterProfilerData.cs
Despite being an 'as' clause an exception of type 'System.Collections.Generic.KeyNotFoundException'" is thrown for 'characterInfo["Talents"]'

This also happens in RAWR 2.3.5

So sad.
I still can't optimize my banked gear.
Hoped it will work in 2.3.5
